* Accounting Corruption *                 -*-muse-*-

Kasey,

I've identified the fix for the AccountingCorruption alert.  Here is the diff of the change that
will fix the issue in 6.0 3001.

I spoke with Eric about this and he decided to hold this fix off until 7.0 release.  I'm going to
change the filter on the server to call it a Warning.

I am currently unable to run the unit tests on either of my machines since I have upgraded them.
Eventually these will get fixed but for now I can compile successfully but not run unit testing.

Also when trying to pull code from the "6.0-3001" branch I get the following message:
Your configuration specifies to merge with the ref '6.0-3001'
from the remote, but no such ref was fetched.

When I moved forward to the master branch I noticed that this area of the code has changed enough
that new learning is required.

Rather than continue to invest in keeping the machines, repos, and knowledge synched up, it makes
more ecconomic sense to have you add this to your list.  I figure just getting back into the code,
after being out of it for several months, is going to probably take a couple days.

I hate to dump another thing on you, but I think it is best for Watermill.

Thanks.
Mark



